* requires *
python 2.x
python-yaml
python-notify
pyhton-feedparser

via package manager or pip (python-pip)

*Configuration file*
add feeds into
~/.rssNotifier.yaml 
like following
channels:
- enabled: true
  name: barsport
  url: http://xliguria.it/rubriche/barsport/feed/
  icon: "/usr/share/OpenGenova/scripts/xliguria.png"
- enabled: true
  name: ladyp
  url: http://xliguria.it/rubriche/ladyp/feed/
- enabled: false
  name: pausacafe
  url: http://xliguria.it/rubriche/pausacafe/feed/ 

Pay attention that the example into the repository does not contains the first dot "." into the name.

To start it at desktop login, copy the file "xliguria.desktop" into ~/.config/autostart, "rssNotifier.py" into "/usr/share/OpenGenova/scripts", fix channel icons path in your configuration file, and you are done.

